Plugins used

Advanced Locomotion System v4 （ALSv4 is recommended as a plugin but not mandatory; you can opt for other character movement systems besides ALSv4.）


Kung Fu PK-MAN is a fully fleshed-out Kung Fu character, serving as the main character in the game, featuring four styles of totem designs - Chinese, Japanese, American, and Punk.


The KFP character is equipped with a toxin-resistant helmet, backpack, bombs, and four levels of metallic weapons. The character possesses muscle deformation and 52 basic facial expression deformations. A straightforward character blueprint controls the character components and material properties like bloodstains, dirt marks, watermarks, and other material options.


Included is a tutorial demonstration on integrating the KFP character blueprint into the ALSv4 advanced character movement system, with adaptability to other motion systems following the tutorial's instructions.


The helmet boasts a selection of 12 masks, and the character offers 12 facial warpaint options.


The highly adjustable material sphere allows for modifications to nearly 90% of parameters in material management, covering style totems, dust, bloodstains, oil marks, watermarks, freckles, bloodshot eyes, lip colors, and smoky eye prints. Clothing and various props are equipped with color IDs.


Alterations in AO after prop changes are also pre-set within the blueprint.
